init_text:
Should Schools Provide Free Pads and Tampons?

Have you ever experienced period shaming, or “period poverty”? Should schools step in to help? Should schools be required to provide free pads and tampons to students? How are pads and tampons similar to toilet paper, soap, Band-Aids and other products that are already provided in schools? How are they different?

---

In my opinion,

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: the answer to all of these questions is a sturdy “No”.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: If such a mechanism were in place, I’d be all for schools providing free pads and tampons.

actions.text: Having discussed the topic honestly, with girls in a comfortable atmosphere and then only having to deal with girls who have been surprised by their first period

actions.text: I don’t think that it is appropriate to educate girls about menstruation in a group setting.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Without a doubt, the value and importance of education is and will be fundamentally tied to our ability to arm our young people with facts.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: In an ideal world, every young woman would have at least one good parent or guardian who teaches her about menstruation.
